</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-btwLGw cuLvxI pf-49_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-50_ pf-text-1"><strong>Health and Safety (First-aid) Regulations 1981</strong> - These regulations require all educational establishments to have adequate first aid equipment, facilities, and personnel tailored to each institution's circumstances.












</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-52_ pf-text-1"><strong>Management of Health and Safety at Work Regulations 1999</strong> - These stress the importance of risk assessments in educational settings to determine first aid needs.












</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-54_ pf-text-1"><strong>Care Quality Commission (CQC) and Ofsted Requirements </strong>- These bodies set guidelines and standards for safety and care in educational contexts, underlining the necessity for proper first aid training and resources.













